OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F389A1783950571
OL,3,CFormer colleagues remember Ann
OL,4,CWiddecombe in the town she was MP in
OL,5,Cfor 23 years
OL,7,FShe added: "I shall always remember
OL,8,Fher in her battle bus with a massive
OL,9,Fmegaphone - she had a very big voice
OL,10,Ffor a small lady - shouting at the top
OL,11,Fof her voice, 'Vote Conservative, vote
OL,12,FConservative today', and beeping her
OL,13,Fhorn.
OL,15,F"And that will be my memory of Ann.
OL,16,FShe was very good with me, very fair -
OL,17,Fmay she rest in peace."
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/4
